programme.title: Whip It
programme.desc: Bliss Cavendar (Ellen Page) es una joven que crece en un pequeño pueblo de Texas, entre los partidos de fútbol de su padre Earl (Daniel Stern) y los concursos de belleza de su madre (Marcia Gay Harden). Un panorama desolador. Bliss está harta de todo eso y encuentra consuelo en su amiga Pash (Alia Shawkat), quien le propone una opción para escapar de ese mundo de tristeza y entender el sentido real de la vida

programme.title: The Breakfast Club
programme.desc: Teen-angst comedy drama. Five total strangers - an athlete, a spoiled rich kid, a brainy nerd, an introverted loner and a rebellious punk - are brought together on a day-long detention where they break the rules, bare their souls and find they have more in common than just attending the same high school. One of the plethora of 80s teen films, John Hughes's bittersweet 'brat pack' comedy has many perceptive moments

programme.title: Selena
programme.desc: Biopic of the Tejano singer who was gunned down by an assistant at the height of her fame. The focus is primarily on Selena's relationship with her family, including her demanding manager-father, and her rise to stardom

programme.title: Crimes and Misdemeanors
programme.desc: A married New York ophthalmologist tries to break up with his mistress, who threatens to tell his wife. Meanwhile, his mob-connected brother offers to "make the problem go away."

programme.title: Happy Tears
programme.desc: Sisters Jayne (Parker Posey) and Laura (Demi Moore) reunite in Pittsburgh to care for their father, whose poor health hasn't stopped him from pursuing a romance with a suspicious woman (Ellen Barkin), much to the consternation of the two sisters. Rip Torn

programme.title: Lucas
programme.desc: Teen charmer about friendships and first loves among a trio of high schoolers

programme.title: Everything Must Go
programme.desc: An alcoholic businessman holds a garage sale after being fired from his job and thrown out of the house along with his belongings by his fed-up wife. While living on his front lawn, he unexpectedly makes friends with a neighbourhood kid and tries to reconnect with a girl he loved in high school

programme.title: Nocturnal Animals
programme.desc: An art-gallery owner reads a novel written by her ex-husband, and becomes greatly disturbed by the possibility that the story was inspired by their marriage and that her safety is in jeopardy

programme.title: The Outsiders
programme.desc: Members of rival local gangs, distinguished by the haves and the have-nots, get into a scuffle that results in death in 1960s Oklahoma

programme.title: Hoffa
programme.desc: The life of powerful union leader Jimmy Hoffa is the subject of this biographical drama. The focus is strongly on Hoffa's public and political life, from his early days as a labour organizer to his later conflicts with the Federal government -- and, eventually, his mysterious disappearance. A film based on the story of legendary union figure Jimmy Hoffa

programme.title: Hoffa

The focus is strongly on Hoffa's public and political life, from his early days as a labour organizer to his later conflicts with the Federal government -- and, eventually, his mysterious disappearance. A film based on the story of legendary union figure Jimmy Hoffa

programme.title: Cake
programme.desc: A woman suffering from chronic pain starts seeing hallucinations of a young wife who committed suicide. Later, she gets to know the latter's husband and faces her own inner demons

programme.title: The Big Lebowski
programme.desc: Jeff Bridges is Jeff 'The Dude' Leboswki who's mistaken for Jeffrey Lebowski, who is The Big Lebowski. Which explains why he's roughed up and his rug pissed on. In search of recompense, The Dude tracks down his namesake, who instead offers him a job. His wife has been kidnapped and he needs a reliable bagman. Aided and hindered by his pals Walter Sobchak, a Vietnam vet, and Donny, master of stupidity, The Dude finds himself involved in violence, mayhem and bowling rivalry with Jesus Quintana in another Coen Brothers classic

programme.title: Adaptation
programme.desc: A screenwriter tries to adapt a bestseller about a real-life orchid thief, but his neuroses get in the way of his writing. When his identical twin brother moves in and decides to become a writer, Charlie finds it even harder to finish his screenplay, a challenge made worse by his growing obsession with the original work's author

programme.title: Adam
programme.desc: This character study stars Hugh Dancy as Adam, a man living with Asperger's syndrome, who does his best to reach out to his pretty new upstairs neighbor. As Adam attempts to gain control of his social skills, he discovers that with a little patience and understanding, developing a meaningful relationship might not be as hard as he previously thought. Peter Gallagher, Amy Irving, Rose Byrne

programme.title: Nell
programme.desc: A young woman living in an isolated North Carolina cabin is discovered by a small-town doctor, who is fascinated by her and attempts to introduce her to the world. Based on the play "Idioglossia" by Mark Handley

programme.title: Elizabeth
programme.desc: Cate Blanchett reprises her role as Queen Elizabeth I in this account of her efforts to defend England from King Philip II of Spain, while trying to suppress her attraction to the dashing Sir Walter Raleigh

programme.title: The Book of Eli
programme.desc: Post-apocalyptic action about a solitary warrior who fights to protect the last known copy of a powerful book. Decades after a nuclear war, a lone man calling himself Eli trudges through the dilapidated cities and scorched wilderness of America, carrying his copy of the Bible, a sacred book that provides 'contentment for the weak-minded'. On an odyssey to bring the text to a sacred place, Eli brings God's wrath down on the robbers, murderers and rapists who lie in wait along the highways. Driven by faith and divine calling, Eli's endeavour becomes harder when he meets the power-hungry Carnegie, who tutors an army of psychopathic rogues and gunmen in a small town. Hoping to steal the book he believes is his last chance to rule what is left of humanity, Carnegie sets out to catch Eli, while Carnegie's step-daughter also follows Eli on his quest. As Carnegie and his henchmen hunt Eli down, they soon discover what a powerful and fearsome adversary he really is

programme.title: Lost River
programme.desc: A financially strapped single mother descends into a dark world in order to protect her family. Meanwhile, her son confronts the town bully and discovers a hidden utopia

programme.title: Here on Earth
programme.desc: After crashing his car in a small town, a spoiled rich kid falls for a local beauty but faces competition from her boyfriend

programme.title: About a Boy
programme.desc: Adaptation of the Nick Hornby novel about the friendship that develops between a bright but awkward 12-year-old boy and a wayward thirtysomething man masquerading as a lone parent in a bid to seduce single mothers. Ironically, it is the boy who initiates the bachelor into the world of adult responsibility and meaningful relationships as the bond between them deepens

programme.title: Something's Gotta Give
programme.desc: Harry is an aging Casanova who refuses to accept his old age and Erica is an acclaimed dramatist. Certain unavoidable circumstances force them to share a roof, even though they are so different

programme.title: Rules Don't Apply
programme.desc: In 1958 Hollywood, a romance blossoms between a pious actress and a right-wing chauffeur—even though both of them work for reclusive billionaire Howard Hughes, who forbids his employees to date each other. Their secret liaison plays out while Hughes' aviation innovations keep pace with his debilitating eccentricities

programme.title: Envy
programme.desc: Two best friends who are also neighbors and coworkers have a falling out after one has multimillion-dollar success with a far-fetched consumer product that hits the big time and the other fails to invest in the dubious solvent, leaving him out of money

programme.desc: Two best friends who are also neighbors and coworkers have a falling out after one has multimillion-dollar success with a far-fetched consumer product that hits the big time and the other fails to invest in the dubious solvent, leaving him out of money

programme.title: Kinsey
programme.desc: Provocative, intelligent biopic starring Liam Neeson as pioneering sex researcher Alfred Kinsey and Laura Linney as his freethinking wife. Chris O'Donnell, Peter Sarsgaard, Timothy Hutton, John Lithgow, Tim Curry. Directed by Bill Condon

programme.title: Tightrope
programme.desc: A cop is put on the line when evidence ties him to the prostitute murders he's investigating. Meanwhile, the culprit is likely an S&M fetishist, like the cop

programme.title: Underworld
programme.desc: Fantasy about a centuries-old war between vampires and werewolves, and an unsuspecting human who is entangled in their conflict

programme.title: House of Sand and Fog
programme.desc: A recovering alcoholic tries to reclaim her bungalow from the Iranian-American couple who bought it at auction. The former owner feels the county took her property away unjustly and wants it back. She hires a lawyer to plead her case, but since the new owners have not broken the law, both sides become involved in a difficult moral dilemma

programme.title: The Bourne Identity
programme.desc: A blockbuster hit, The Bourne Identity stars Academy Award®-winner Matt Damon as a man fished out of the ocean by an Italian boat who has a complete loss of memory. Why are assassins after him? Why is he a master of martial arts and fluent in several languages? The answers will thrill and astonish you! Featuring amazing action scenes, taut direction, and beautiful European locations, The Bourne Identity is the opening introduction to a hugely popular action espionage franchise. Starring Matt Damon, Chris Cooper, Franka Potente, Julia Stiles

programme.title: In the Valley of Elah
programme.desc: Riveting fact-based drama about a Vietnam war veteran (Tommy Lee Jones) who goes on a quest to find his soldier son, who disappeared after returning stateside from a tour of duty in Iraq. Susan Sarandon, Charlize Theron. Written and directed by Paul Haggis

programme.title: Abandon
programme.desc: A bright college student is haunted by her past in this thriller. Katie Burke is a driven senior at a prestigious college whose boyfriend, Embry, vanished years earlier. Katie's life unravels when a cop investigates the disappearance and Embry begins showing up on campus

programme.title: Jackie
programme.desc: In the immediate aftermath of the assassination of President John F. Kennedy, his wife Jacqueline deals with her immense grief while caring for her young family and making plans for his funeral procession. At the same time, a bereaved nation watches on

programme.title: Erin Brockovich
programme.desc: Erin Brockovich is an unemployed single mother, desperate to find a job, but is having no luck.While no one takes her seriously, with her trashy clothes and earthy manners, that soon changes when she begins to investigate a suspicious real estate case involving the Pacific Gas & Electric Company. What she discovers is that the company is trying quietly to buy land that was contaminated by hexavalent chromium, and, in turn, poisoning the residents in the area. As she digs deeper, Erin finds herself leading point in a series of events that would involve her lawfirm in one of the biggest class action lawsuits in American history against a multi-billion dollar corporation

programme.title: Taken
programme.desc: Liam Neeson stars as former CIA operative Bryan Mills, who's desperate to track down his kidnapped daughter in Pierre Morel's Luc Besson-produced action-thriller. Mills' life hasn't panned out well; his dedication to the CIA wrecked his marriage and made him neglect his daughter Kim. Now, retired from the Agency, he wants to make things up to Kim. But to do so, he has to contend with his ex-wife's animosity and Kim's new step-father's wealth. So when he has an opportunity to advance Kim's pop star ambitions he jumps at the chance, even if that means her and a friend crossing the Atlantic to brave 'the dangers of Europe'. As things turn out, he has a point: in Paris, the two girls are kidnapped by vicious Eastern European sex traffickers. As they are being abducted, Bryan tells one of the baddies, via Kim's mobile phone: 'I will look for you, I will find you, and I will kill you'. He subsequently does his best to make good on his promise, using all the violent tricks of the trade his time at the CIA taught him(n)

programme.title: The Hangover
programme.desc: The guests are set to arrive. The bride is getting ready. But the best man has lost the groom! When three friends get together for one last weekend-long bachelor party in Vegas, they think they had a good time. But it's very hard to remember, and they are suffering the dreadful after-effects of girls, party and alcohol. And then they realize they have somehow lost the groom! Now, they must struggle to retrace their wild weekend to find their friend and deliver the bridegroom to his wedding -- even as they suffer from one killer Hangover!(n)

programme.title: 15 Minutes
programme.desc: A New York detective and an arson investigator go after a pair of Eastern European killers who manipulate the media(n)

programme.title: Step Up
programme.desc: A sullen young thug named Tyler winds up doing community service at the Baltimore High School for the Performing Arts. At first he's just smirking and mopping the floors, but then Nora, a talented dancer and choreographer, loses her partner to a fractured ankle mere weeks before the big showcase, and Tyler steps in as her partner. At first he doesn't take it too seriously but then again, he's never had a real chance in life. His best friend from the street gets jealous..(n)

programme.title: Public Enemies
programme.desc: sonDirector Michael Mann's historical crime drama follows the efforts of top FBI agent Melvin Purvis (Christian Bale) in capturing notorious bank robber John Dillinger (Johnny Depp). A folk hero to the American public, Dillinger was virtually unstoppable at the height of his criminal career. J. Edgar Hoover's FBI was just being formed, and in order to turn his fledgling agency into a national police force, Hoover recruits Purvis to catch the most-elusive criminal in the country(n)

programme.title: Mickey Blue Eyes
programme.desc: A British expat working in Manhattan as an auctioneer falls in love with a mobster's daughter. When he tries to ingratiate himself with her family, he ends up involved in criminal activity and is forced to pose as a wiseguy from Kansas City(n)

programme.title: Lowriders
programme.desc: An aimless young street artist in L.A. named Danny finds himself torn between the lowrider car culture of his father and his desire for a creative outlet. This generational clash is further complicated when Danny's older brother returns home from prison(n)

programme.title: Love Liza
programme.desc: Character actor extraordinaire Philip Seymour Hoffman stars as a man grappling with his wife's suicide in this incisive character study written by his brother Gordy. Kathy Bates is memorable as his mother-in-law. Denny: Jack Kehler. Maura: Sarah Koskoff. Bailey: Stephen Tobolowsky. Brenda: Erika Alexander. Bern: J.D. Walsh. Pad: Jimmy Raskin. Jim: Kevin Breznahan. Lynne: Jennifer Keddy. Directed by Todd Louiso(n)

programme.title: Confidence
programme.desc: Well-made but derivative crime drama about a cocky grifter (Edward Burns) trying to make amends after accidentally ripping off a powerful L.A. underworld boss (Dustin Hoffman). Directed by James Foley. Screenplay by Doug Jung(n)

programme.title: The American President
programme.desc: Andrew Shepherd is approaching the end of his first term as President of the United States. He's a widower with a young daughter and has proved to be popular with the public. His election seems assured. That is until he meets Sydney Ellen Wade, a paid political activist working for an environmental lobby group. He's immediately smitten with her and after several amusing attempts, they finally manage to go on a date (which happens to be a State dinner for the visiting President of France). His relationship with Wade opens the door for his prime political opponent, Senator Bob Rumson, to launch an attack on the President's character, something he could not do in the previous election as Shepherd's wife had only recently died(n)

programme.title: Extreme Measures
programme.desc: A brilliant emergency-room physician (Hugh Grant) stumbles across a doctor's diabolical experiment involving humans. Gene Hackman. Jodie: Sarah Jessica Parker. Hare: David Morse. Directed by Michael Apted(n)

programme.title: Extreme Ops
programme.desc: Extreme-sports enthusiasts run afoul of a slippery terrorist and his henchmen while filming a commercial in the Austrian Alps. Slick action, absurd plot. Devon Sawa, Rufus Sewell, Bridgette Wilson-Sampras

programme.title: Terminator Salvation
programme.desc: Director McG takes the helm for the fourth instalment of the sci-fi action franchise, starring Christian Bale and Sam Worthington. The principal action takes place in the not-too-distant 2018, in the devastated world that was glimpsed early in the series, where a determined group of resistance fighters are battling killing machines that are set on sole control of the planet. Joining Consolidated Companies as a secretary, she is taken under the wing of super-efficient, long-time office manager VIolet Newstead and fellow secretary Doralee Rhodes (Parton, in her screen debut). The trio have the misfortune of working for Franklin Hart Jr - a first class chauvinist, who will quite happily tip pencils on the floor just so he can ogle Rhodes's cleavage while she picks them up. When Newstead is unfairly passed over for promotion for the umpteenth time, the women head for Doralee's house to commiserate and smoke pot, which prompts revenge fantasies from each of them. But then fantasy blends with reality, and events spin out of control for the trio..

They met at an auction in Nantucket one rainswept afternoon seventeen years ago, bidding against each other for the same ivory figurine, and instantly fell in love. He was a brilliant law student at Harvard, and she, a college girl and star gymnast. They were soon married and had two wonderful children. As Oliver becomes more successful, his recognition of his wife's separate identity dwindles to the danger point. Although she has everything she could possibly want, Barbara wants more and decides to start a catering company which turns out to be a great success. The film opens at a party for Manhattan yuppie Rob Hawkins where the revelries are interrupted by a loud explosion. As he and his friends Hud, Jason, Marlena and Lily emerge onto the street, the head of the Statue of Liberty cartwheels past them. Something very big, scaly and angry is trashing the city, and one of the targets is a high-rise where Beth, Rob's girlfriend lives. The group set out in a rescue bid, with Hud recording everything as they make their way through what has become a nightmarish New York, threatened both by the monster (only ever half-glimpsed, making it even more terrifying) and the parasitic lice it sheds, which develop a taste for human flesh. Will all, or indeed any, of the group make it to safety? The footage tells their stories in shocking, handheld detail in this superbly paced movie

programme.title: The Taking of Pelham 1 2 3
programme.desc: The late Tony Scott's remake of the 1974 thriller, starring John Travolta and Denzel Washington. It's a day that the passengers on a New York subway train are unlikely to forget. And it's one that could rescue the professional life of subway employee Walter Garber, whose glittering career has been derailed by allegations of corruption. Garber is languishing on duty as a train dispatcher when all hell breaks loose after one of the Lexington Avenue line trains is hijacked by a gang led by the supremely self-assured, calmly ruthless Ryder. Ryder issues a demand for $10m and makes it clear that he won't hesitate to kill anyone who gets in his way. Garber and NYPD hostage negotiator Lieutenant Camonetti attempt to get to grips with the crisis but, as events progress, suspicions arise as to whether there's more to the hijacking than first meets the eye. Also starring James Gandolfini as New York's mayor and Luis Guzmán as a disgruntled subway worker who has joined Ryder's gang(n)
